Pre-Game Insights: Germany manager Julian Nagelsmann is likely to hand full debuts to at least two players in Friday's UEFA Nations League clash with Bosnia-Herzegovina in Zenica.
Germany have already lost five players to injury this month, including Arsenal's Kai Havertz and Bayern Munich's Jamal Musiala.
Benjamin Henrichs, David Raum, and Robin Koch have also withdrawn from the October squad.
Other key names such as Niclas Fullkrug and Marc-Andre ter Stegen are absent from the ranks this month.
With neither Ter Stegen nor the retired Manuel Neuer available, 34-year-old Oliver Baumann is expected to make his senior debut in goal.
Antonio Rudiger, Joshua Kimmich, Jonathan Tah, and Maximilian Mittelstadt are fit and firing.
Robert Andrich and Pascal Gross could form the two-man midfield pairing.
Florian Wirtz will no doubt occupy one of the advanced positions, and Serge Gnabry could hold off the threat of Kevin Schade to start on the left.

Deniz Undav is Germany's chief attacking threat, and the one-time Brighton & Hove Albion man may be joined by the uncapped Jonathan Burkardt, who boasts five goals from his first six Bundesliga appearances of the season for Mainz 05.
